HEADWORD: Dusken
<hw>Dusk"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make dusk or
obscure.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not utterly defaced, but only <qex>duskened</qex>.</q>
